#filter substitution
.TH nightingale "1" "MARCH 2014" "@NG_VERSION@"
.SH NAME
nightingale \- Desktop Media Player
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B nightingale [\fR \fIoptions \fR... \fB] [\fR\fIurl\fR\fB|\fR\fIpath\fR\fB]

.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBnightingale\fR is a desktop media player, a digital jukebox and web browser mash-up.
It supports extensions and skins feathers. Like Firefox/Iceweasel, it is built
from the Mozilla cross-platform and open source framework, based on Songbird.

.SH OPTIONS
The following options are provided by \fBnightingale\fR using the standard GNU
command line syntax:
.IP
.PP

.SS "X11 options:"
.TP
.B \-\-display\fR=\fIDISPLAY
X display to use
.TP
.B \-\-sync
.br
Make X calls synchronous
.TP
.B \-\-no\-xshm
Don't use X shared memory extension
.TP
.B \-\-xim\-preedit\fR=\fISTYLE
.TP
.B \-\-xim\-status\fR=\fISTYLE
.TP
.B \-\-g\-fatal\-warnings
Make all warnings fatal
.PP

.SS "Nightingale options:"
.TP
.B \-h \fRor\fB \-help
Print a list of available commands.
.TP
.B \-v \fRor\fB \-version
Print Nightingale version.
.TP
.B \-P \fR<profile>
Start with <profile>.
.TP
.B \-migration
Start with migration wizard.
.TP
.B \-ProfileManager
Start with ProfileManager.
.TP
.B \-no\-remote
Open new instance, not a new window in running instance.
.TP
.B \-UILocale \fR<locale>
Start with <locale> resources as UI Locale.
.TP
.B \-safe\-mode
Disables extensions and themes for this session.
.TP
.B \-jsconsole
Open the Error console.
.TP
.B \-test [\fR\fItests\fR\fB]
Run tests on the components listed in the optional comma\-separated list of tests.
If no tests are passed in ALL tests will be run.
.TP
.B [\fIurl\fR\fB|\fR\fIpath\fR\fB]
Local path/filename to media items to import and play, or URL to load in the browser.
.TP
.B \-register\-extensions
Registers extensions and then quits.
.TP
.B \-play
Start or resume playback at the current position.
.TP
.B \-stop
Stop playback.
.TP
.B \-pause
Pause playback.
.TP
.B \-toggle-playback
Starts playback, if there is none and pauses it if media is currently playing.
.TP
.B \-next
Skips to the next item in the sequence.
.TP
.B \-previous
Goes back to the previous item in the sequence.
.TP
.B \-mute
Mute the volume if it's not yet, else unmute it.
.TP
.B \-volumeup
Raise the volume by 10%.
.TP
.B \-volumedown
Lower the volume by 10%.
.TP

.SH BUGS
1. Post on the forum (\fIhttp://forum.getnightingale.com/\fR) or reach us on IRC.
.PP
2. Look on GitHub issues (\fIhttps://github.com/nightingale-media-player/nightingale-hacking/issues\fR)
or the forum if the issue wasn't reported before.
.PP
3. If not, report the bug GitHub issues. Don't forget to include critical information
like operating system, Nigtingale version and how you obtained the Nightingale executable.

